caption: Super good food. Great bartender/manager.
Best pizza in the Boise area. Awesome atmosphere too.
Front Door is one of the best pizzeria I’ve been. The quality of their food and service is amazing, and the prices are unbeatable.
I've ordered a few pizzas from here and have loved all of them. My favorite so far is the Don Kahuna. The $20 large size is pretty massive. I'm happy to have a new go to pizza joint in town!

Had my friends birthday party here, and Brandan W was our server. He did an amazing job with everything. From start to finish Brandan was on point. The food we all got was great. I had the Irish pizza with jalapeños added. Best pizza I have had in many years, as well as the door poppers! Brandan is an outstanding server and the food is great. Why would you not want to have a night out at The Front Door... Thank you much Brandan W.
Favorite pizza around. Always a go to. Great being able to order some Reef as well on the side.
Accidently messed up on order. I called and let them know and they did more than was required to make us happy. Id recommend these guys too everyone. Amazing wise guy pizza here!
Another great lunch from The Front Door. The bacon on the BLT is delicious!
Its the reef for fun and food.
Worth it!

Great pizza, IMHO the best semi-thin crust in town. Get either the 10" or when choosing the larger sizes have them make the crust crispy all the way through and it will come out perfectly crispy from crust to center. Service has always been great over the years regardless of changing faces.

Front Door has pizza. Amazing pizza. You want to know how amazing this pizza place is? I got two word for you, homie; sit down and brace yourself. Macaroni & cheese pizza.  Seriously. And yes, I know, that's technically three words, four if you're one of those mutants that counts "&" as a word just because it is a stand-in for "and". But think about the symmetry of it: macaroni & cheese.  Macaroni..  and cheese  It's one thing. Its one thing all by itself, Macaroni & cheese is its own stand-alone thing, and we all know it. We've known it since childhood.  And someone went and made macaroni & cheese into its own stand-alone pizza topping. I'm not joking! You can get macaroni & cheese pizza at Front Door.  Even a friend from Italy admitted that it was a clever move and worthy of both macaroni & cheese and pizza. Although I think I saw her soul dim slightly in her eyes as she said it. Just a bit. Probably because a thousand years after the Roman Empire, they had not thought of macaroni & cheese pizza themselves despite having all the ingredients right at their fingertips.  But seriously, go forth and eat some macaroni & cheese pizza if you can, and do it now. It comes with bacon, but do what I do and ask for the bacon to be replaced with..  ...wait for it..  ...anchovies.  No, seriously! Just do it! Trust me! You will live your years eternally grateful that you discovered this treasure. If you're feeling super squirrely then also pair this with the Caesar salad with anchovies (this is a test; technically a "Caesar salad" without anchovies is just a boring old regular salad). But no matter. With or without a salad, you have to try the macaroni & cheese pizza with anchovies.  Go forth and enjoy, my friends. Hoist high the banner of the Legion and conquer yourself some pizza, there, Centurion. You will NOT be sorry.
The best pizza in town 😋
Best pizza I’ve found in Boise. Super fresh and great quality, nice staff to boot! My boyfriend and I love this spot as a delicious treat. :)
Already love this place, needed a quick meal and got my order right away, even got a free wing! Thank you guys.

This is my favorite pizza place in town! They have great pizza, good drinks, and it is all reasonably priced. If I had one complaint, it is that there is not enough seating. But I don't think that being popular is a good enough reason to give less than 5 stars. I will always come here when I am in the mood for a fantastic pizza night with friends!
Burger was great, beer selection wide, and service awesome.

Food is pretty good, but service is borderline horrible. Even sitting at the bar... Probably won't be back, gave it two tries but there's just so much better service at too many other places to waste time here

We have always loved this place! Our last visit (3-6-20) was the worst we had. First of all we ordered an appetizer which came after we got our main meal. The server made us feel that we had to take it, since we ordered it. Anyway, it appears the quality of food has gone down hill along with the service. My wife's cocktail  was wrong on the bill, so we do not know if it was the correct price.  I would have expected them to remove the cost of the appetizer or offer a free beer or something.... There was no apology or anything. Do not know what has happened there, but we will be spending our money at other places. All we were doing was looking to have a nice meal, which did not happen.
The wife and I had a very nice time here. Our wait staff was very knowelgeable on microbrews. She was able to pick brews that I was looking for. Pizza was excellent. We will go back.

Low key the best pizza in Boise. Plus, a nice selection of beers and sours. If you're willing to wait, they'll start slinging slices after 9pm. Couple slices and a beer and there's your Saturday night.
Perfect atmosphere!!
Love their pizza and salads.

Went there for a special birthday lunch with friends.  The food was amazing.  I had the coconut curry special and it was perfectly seasoned.  The wait staff was quick and courteous and met all our needs. This place is a downtown favorite of mine because of the food, the staff, and the ambiance.
Amazing yumminess!
Great pizza, great beer selection

INCREDIBLE pizza! Maybe the best pizza place in Boise. They also have tons of fantastic drinks to choose from if you're looking for a place to get a few good drinks. The staff is very educated on their drinks and very attentive and helpful. Love coming here.
Really good food for lunch.  Staff is super friendly.

Ordered for the first time last night. The pizza was amazing, ready on time and delicious. Maybe a bit too much sugar but good. The issue I have is with the “jumbo” wings for about $1.59 a piece or something. They are, in fact, not jumbo anything. They are wingettes... they are just flat pieces. For. A. Whole. Dollar. And. Change. With a 3 order minimum to order. Just create wing combos at that point and price them responsibly. I ordered five expecting a WING and DRUM attached together. It barely amounts to an appetizer, if you can call it that, at 5pcs.
Really good pizza!

They always have good pizza either with their lunch special or get a whole pie.  Nice crisp crust and fresh ingredients.  Most of all is their great beer selection, they usually have beer you won't find elsewhere in town and top it all off with beer savvy staff.  The best is having lunch or dinner outside in their patio.
This place has hands down the best pizza West of the Mississippi! I've traveled the world and highly recommend The Front Door!
Brandon white is the bomb tried his pizza and being a native New Yorker and this such good pizza. And hospitality is amazing ❤️
Possibly the best sandwich there is but the service is, without fault, dismally slow.
Great place to go to spend $7.50 for a beer
My new favorite pizza place! They use the best ingredients and have a really cool atmosphere. I'll definitely be back!
Great service, great food and great drinks!
We had Italian cheese dunkers — YUM !! Great beer, cool atmosphere above average pizza ❤️

After a long day of roadtripping, nothing sounded better than a hot melty slice of pizza and boy this this joint deliver; the Mac pizza really hit the spot!  Amazing service!  Give this place a try, you’ll be impressed!
Excellent service. Friendly employees and great pizza.

Our whole family has loved going to the Front Door for about 10 years. Some of the best pizza in town, great prices, and fun, casual atmosphere. The more than respectable beer selection has kept us going back. We were disappointed that the newer vibe appears to be "sports bar" with max TV volume  There are large screens in all four corners of the dining room. No problem there - until the speakers are so loud you can't even hear the people sitting at your table. While we had yummy food there tonight, we definitely did not enjoy the ambiance.

I was in Boise on business and just happened to walk by this place. My first impression was not one of a pizza place. I saw just another bar slinging microbrews and passing off bar food as restaurant cuisine. At the end of my meal, I found nothing to convince me otherwise.  If you can put yourself in this mindset Front Door does offer slightly above average pub grub and reasonable prices. I had a cobb salad. This is my go-to meal when on the road and in a new place. The service was quick and the meal enjoyable. Overall I found Front Door a nice enough place for either a quick meal or a place to hang out and have a few drinks.
Best pizza in Boise!
Small joint but cozy. My favorite pizza in Boise. Great crust, little crunchy yet chewy. Good beer selection and friendly service
Best pizza we have had in Boise.

Nice pub style, neighborhood atmosphere. Wait staff very friendly. Had a personal pizza (mac n cheese) that was excellent. Not too heavy on the macaroni, almost a thin crust. It was excellent. Great selection of local brews on tap. Very knowledgeable bartender. Streetside parking and wheelchair accessible.
Pizza is fantastic and the prices are very reasonable. Staff is friendly and the place is comfortable. TV's with sports and a good tap list. Definitely will return.
Jose is the best bar tender I've ever had!!!!!!

this is my comfy retreat in Boi. food is on point, awesome happy hour, and it feels like the servers are my friends. user beware... the nachos are like no other, but absolutely NOT for one...bring friends. dont get me started on the mac and cheese pizza, oh my
Pizza was really good. Don't think I got prosciutto though, just regular ham. A bit pricey. Waitress forgot our beers. Not impressed, but food was tasty.
No superma=ket beer here...many options on tap.  Exceplent crust on pizza.  Will be back.

Consistent quality and service.

I used to like the front door, not anymore. A week and a half ago my wife and I ordered the mac and cheese pizza. Because my wife is vegetarian we ordered it with only half bacon. When we finally got it, it was half jalapeno and bacon covering it all. I immediately called them and let them know of the error. Also instead of the sweet chile bacon, it was regular ground up bacon. My wife was hungry after not eating most of the day and they said they would mail out a coupon for a free pizza because my wife was going to try and pick out the bacon. Never received the coupon and my wife couldn't eat the pizza.
Very fun and unique menu.  I liked the macaroni pizza!  Staff was attentive and prompt.  Drink selections were fresh and full of variety.  We will definitely be back.
Came in to list order a pizza and they took over an hour
Front Door has awesome pizza as well as sandwiches and salads. Tuesday night they offer calzones so that's the night to go in.
Love this place.  Great pizza. Awesome service.  Will return again and again.
Subs are awesome
Good pizza here
Decent apps, good pizza, and generally a nice selection of beer. The bottled selection of beers usually includes some good Austrian and German selections.

Brandon is super rad - he takes good care of his customers. This is easily in the top 3 best pizza spots in Boise. I’ve loved everything I’ve tried here. They make everything in house, quality ingredients, and a good drinks selection. I’ll be back soon.
Great pizza and beer.
Always superb service and food.

The Front Door is a hidden gem in downtown Boise. The ambiance and vibe of this little pizza place is the perfect spot to enjoy some great food and friendly service. The food is very consistent and always delicious. Their beer selection is very diverse and rotates regularly so you can always find something new to try. They also have a full bar! I'm never disappointed when I grab a bite at Front Door!
Love this place. Great pizza and my fav bartender is jose 👍
The best pizza.  Great staff

Great friendly service. We had a great social meetup of our club for pizza.
First time and I'm definitely going back. Their pizza is to die for!

Excellent pizza!
Great food good music and an amazing staff!!!

This is a small cozy fun bar with really good food, drinks,  and TV. I have had the ceasar salad, italian sandwitch, and enforcer sandwitch which were amazing tasting and perfect . It is reasonable priced for the high quality food. Staff is solid and the wait time is very small.

This was the best pizza I have had in years. Brandon was a great host and bartender and suggested a half and half pizza which was amazing! I will definitely make this a regular stop on every repeat trip to Boise!
One of my favorite pizza places :) The jalapeno poppers were AWESOME!!! The pizza and service was EXCELLENT! Great job Jose and Ali for your excellent service :)

This place was great! There is a great selection of beers and food. Our server was also excellent and suggested getting half and half pizzas so we could enjoy some of each. Everyone enjoyed them. The jalepeno popper app was also excellent. Definitely will be returning!

Wonderful tap rotation and fantastic pizza, although be prepared for char. That's just how Front Door does it. The sandwiches/wraps/salads are pretty good too. Ask about what specials they run through the week at lunch.
Great crust. Toppings are unique but great tasting.
One of our go to places. Highly recommend the Enforcer!
Awesome pizza!!

I really like this spot. Their apps are delicious and their pies are very good. Huge rotating beer selection so you can try something new each time. Servers are always friendly and attentive. A go to spot for my wife and I when we are hanging out downtown.
Got some pizza with coworkers due to recommendation of one of them. Their claim was that it was the best pizza in Boise. After trying it most of us agreed with that claim. Staff was very friendly.

Awesome pizza. Nice staff.  Pretty little town.
Consistently great food. Salads. Sandwiches. Pizzas. Great selection of beers. Full bar. Go.

While the food was decent, it is WAY over priced. We ordered a large 1/2 & 1/2 pizza. It was $18.95  base price plus $2.50 per topping. For a total of $36.45!! The waitress did not explain pricing and neither did the menu. Talked to her and her manager. He claimed he built our pizza himself and that he used the same amount of toppings for each half that he would on a whole pizza. If that’s the case they skimp on the toppings! Will not return.

Great pizza and great beer. They have wines too but I'm a beer drinker. Entrance is hard to spot at first but it's one of my favorite pizza joints.

My wife and I finally had the chance to check this place out.  We were not disappointed!  Delicious pizza with perfect crust and generous toppings.  The beer was good, too. ;)  She had The Irish.  Basically a loaded baked potato on a pizza.  It didn't sound good to me, but it was!  She loved it, too, while I enjoyed The Boss, with it's double-cut Pepperoni.
Great pizza, great cocktails and great service!! Haley was amazing and so friendly, top notch service! Our go to place for girls night!

Food was great! Very savory, I drank two gallons of water while there. Their loaded won-ton nachos off of the appetizer menu were phenomenal and could easily be a meal for two people alone. The service was kind and the pizza was divine. The ambiance leaned towards the college crowd so I can imagine that it gets pretty busy after a Boise State game.

Pizza had what looked like black pepper on it but turned out to be burned ash from the oven, left a bitter taste in my mouth and upset stomach. Otherwise it could have been a good pizza. First time I have eaten here and also the last time.
Excellent, wood-fired type pizza. A number.of different pies make good use of their extensive array of unusual toppings.
Best pizza in town, friendly service
Mac'n Cheese pizza! Wow!!

This place was the bomb! Never eaten here before and decided to try this place because we heard it was good! And it sure was!  We decided to sit outside and enjoy the weather one last time before it got too cold and it was nice. The inside definitely looks clean and well taken care of and the overall atmosphere is calm and relaxing when we went.  The food was fantastic. The salad was amazing, the pizza was cooked to perfection, and just the garlic bread was enough to keep me coming back. You guys know your food and I'll tell you, it was amazing!  But that's not even the best part about this place! The service we received was above and beyond. I haven't had service this good in forever! That's what really set you guys apart. Unfortunately we didn't get the gentleman's name that took care of our table but from our conversation, he was pretty new to Idaho still (hope you like it here!)  Anyways, you guys definitely have a new and returning customer because of a standard in service you provided to me tonight. Give that man a raise and have him train others! He knows what he is doing! It was excellent!
Great service and amazing beer options. Would definitely recommend. This place deserves more attention!

Great pizza. Try the Mac and cheese one

Delicious pizza, and a good beer selection
Every time I come to Boise I HAVE to hit up the Front Door! Best Pizza Ever! the Enforcer is hands down one of the most enjoyable things I've ever put in my mouth. lol
The food and craft beer are both excellent. Hey here early to get a seat, or stop by late for a slice.

This review could be much higher if it was only based on the first time I came out.  I had the mac and cheese, and it was phenomenal. Some of the best mac and cheese I have ever had.   The cheese was perfectly melted and creamy and all the flavors came through.  Then I came a week later expecting the same result and was utterly disappointed.  The cheese was lumpy and did not have the same texture.  I am surprised I am giving them 3 stars because of the inconsistencies.  I will attempt the mac and cheese one more time and the stars will change based on the next experience.

I always just came here for the beer selection but we decided to get some pizzas this time. The macaroni and cheese pizza may be the best thing I have ever eaten. The bacon was sweet and complimented the mac and cheese perfectly. The crust was amazing! You won't leave any "bones" behind when you eat this pizza. We also had the Thai pizza which cured  the Thai food craving I was having.
Awesome happy hour. Love the pizza and soup.
Good pizza and good top menu. Invoices historic downtown Basque district.

Service was exceptionally long. Everything from getting menus, ordering, and receiving the pizza all took longer than expected (almost 2 hours from start to finish). Watched one couple get up and leave after the waiter said he would get them some menus and did not return. I hate leaving a place knowing I made an order but I really should have got up and gone to a different restaurant. Learned my lesson.  The pizza actually had a good flavor and crust, however the appetizer was just 'ok!' The presentation of the poppers looked nice but it all seemed colder than I would expect for coming out of the oven.  If I could have done it over again I would have gone somewhere else and not wasted my time there.

Ordered a personal pan pizza ,"The Boss". It was terrific! They have a robust sauce and thick, hearty gourmet cheeses that is only accentuated by the brick - oven toasted hand made crust and garnished with basil. An enormous variety of beers, as long as you're not looking for Bud Light. Many local and regional brews for all discerning palates.
Great food, good service, good beer selection!

I LOVE THIS PLACE. I might be a little biased because I used to work here but it is seriously some of the best pizza in Boise! Plus the beer is always fantastic and the people are awesome. I recommend it to everyone!
I stop in for drinks with old friends every couple months and the drinks are always well made and the service is good. They have good pizza, especially after you've been drinking for a few hours. ;-)

This place is fantastic!  The pizzas and sandwiches are unique.  My family and I love coming here for the beer selection, it is almost always different and most are from local breweries.  You definitely don't want to miss out on the Front Door
Best pepperoni in town and amazing tomato basil soup.

This is our regular spot. The staff knows us by name and will always find a beer on tap that we will love! The pizza is great and everything is made from scratch from pizza oven!
